    <briefdescription>
<para>Building topologies by triangles. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This namespace provides API for building meshes.</para>
<para>Simple example with key steps <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">MR::Triangulation<sp/>t;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">t.push_back({0_v,1_v,2_v});<sp/></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">t.push_back({2_v,1_v,3_v});<sp/></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="keyword">auto</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>topology<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="group__GeneralGroup_1gad94b16318381f04c306f214d07b59c3d" kindref="member">MR::MeshBuilder::fromTriangles</ref>(t);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><simplesect kind="warning"><para>Vertices of triangles should have consistent bypass direction</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>It is better to store topology directly in mesh</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classMR_1_1MeshTopology" kindref="compound">MeshTopology</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
